<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/21(Thu.) Declutter your life / Declutter your mind (Host: Sherry)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=336&amp;p=352#p352"><![CDATA[
Session I Declutter your life<br /><br />DECLUTTER YOUR LIFE » 10 questions to ask yourself<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8poA6VWb140">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8poA6VWb140</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Can decluttering your house really make you happier?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20190515-can-decluttering-your-house-really-spark-joy">https://www.bbc.com/future/article/2019 ... -spark-joy</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1: Do you personally know someone who has difficulty throwing away their stuff and always keeps piles of clutter in their home? What are the possible reasons for it? <br /><br />Q2: Do you always “let go” of your surplus belongings you won’t use anymore (from commodities to mementos like photos, books, handwritten cards)?  If not, why do you keep them?  Have you ever felt regret for having thrown off some of your belongings?  What are they and why? <br /><br />Q3: Following the previous question, can collecting these belongings makes our lives better?  Can we be better off with less stuff?  What are the advantages/disadvantages to a simpler and tidier lifestyle?  <br /><br />Q4: Are you good at decluttering your home?  Please share your ways and tips with us.<br /><br /><br />Session II  Declutter your mind<br /><br />How To Declutter Your Mind: 10 Practical Tips You'll Actually Want To Try <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/nomanazish/2017/11/19/how-to-declutter-your-mind-10-practical-tips-youll-actually-want-to-try/#20e7e8424f15">https://www.forbes.com/sites/nomanazish ... e7e8424f15</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />Q5. Have you ever experienced negative thinking in your mind, such as self-pity, self-doubt, worry and rumination that are not helpful to problem solving.  What are they and why did they happen? <br /><br />Q6: Following the previous question, how do you push those disturbing thoughts out of your head?<br /><br />Q7: Do you ever feel like your mind is full of messy work and life tasks, which hinder you from stay focus?  What are they?<br /><br />Q8: The article provides 10 practical tips to help us declutter our mind.  Which do you think is most helpful?  Do you have any other suggestions?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. Free talk<br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. First topic discussion<br />8:10 p.m. --8:40 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Mon Nov 18, 2019 2:13 pm</p><hr />
